OL,3,CRuling for doctor who removed ovaries
OL,4,Cwithout consent appealed
OL,6,FThe proven allegations included
OL,7,Fremoving the ovaries of two patients
OL,8,Fwithout consent, kissing and hugging
OL,9,Fanother patient on two separate
OL,10,Foccasions, and performing multiple
OL,11,Fintimate examinations without a
OL,12,Fchaperone present.
OL,14,FHowever, the tribunal ruled that the
OL,15,Fdoctor's fitness to practise was not
OL,16,Fimpaired and instead issued a warning.
